{
  "texts": [
    "Mutations in lptF were associated with MICs from 8 to >64 mg l -1, and mutant strains retained partial to full virulence in a mouse septicaemia model (Extended Data Table 7).",
    "Mutations in lpxM led to a complete loss of virulence in mice (Extended Data Table 7), consistent with previous report of an in vivo fitness cost in Galleria mellonella 34.",
    "Finally, mutations in adeRS typically resulted in lower fold changes in MIC, with MICs ranging from 1-8 mg l -1 and, in some cases, were not stable when mutant isolates were passaged in the absence of drug pressure.",
    "adeRS mutants retained virulence in mice but, consistent with lower MIC fold increases, also retained susceptibility to zosurabalpin treatment in vivo on the basis of the survival of mice in the treated groups (Extended Data Table 7).",
    "To assess the potential of zosurabalpin for the treatment of severe invasive CRAB infections, its in vitro activity was evaluated against 129 human clinical isolates of A. baumannii derived from a range of infection sites."
  ]
}